latestPosts.caption:
Get ready to go no where and still do your makeup for your mental peace✌🏻 

(Makeup, everyday makeup, grwm, reels, groovy, vibe, 0.5 angle, trending)

They say, “Jack of all trades, master of none.” But in the creative world, that doesn’t quite hold true.
A few days back, I was color grading a video. Adjusting tones, playing with shadows, balancing warmth. And suddenly, it hit me how similar it felt to doing makeup.
Different tools, different mediums, but the eye, the instinct, the sense of harmony — it was all the same.
That’s when I realised again: none of the skills l’ve picked up along the way are random. They connect. They feed each other.
Design helps me style better. Styling helps me think like a photographer. Photography teaches me storytelling. It all circles back.
Being multi-skilled hasn’t scattered my focus. It’s made it sharper.
It’s not about doing everything. It’s about understanding the process so well that when I choose my lane, I know exactly why it’s mine.
Maybe it’s time we rethink what being a jack of all trades really means.
(Also, yes - I created this image by bringing together my skills in photography, styling, adaptability across tools, and a little help from my Al brain🤖) 

|design thinking, designer, AI, versatile designer|
